text: Hamilton County is a county in the U.S. state of Iowa. As of the 2020 census, the population was 15,039. The county seat is Webster City. The county was founded in 1856 and named to honor William W. Hamilton, a President of the Iowa State Senate. == References == Category:1850s establishments in Iowa Category:1856 establishments in the United States Category:Iowa counties
title: Hamilton County, Iowa
